casebody.data:
Mae BURDETTE v. FIRST NATIONAL BANK OF MURPHYSBORO et al. No. 6431. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. Oct. 28, 1937. Soelke, Koehn & Loewy, of Chicago, 111., for appellant. Harold F.- Lindley, of Danville, 111., for appellees.

Before EVANS and SPARKS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of counsel for appelleés, and upon consideration of the certificate of the clérk of the District Court of the United States for the Eastern District of Illinois, it is now here ordered, adjudged, and decreed by this court that this cause be docketed in this court and that this appeal be, and the same is hereby, dismissed, with costs.
